                            <comment id="12855973" author="fs5" created="Mon, 12 Apr 2010 15:05:59 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;&quot;worksforme&quot;-patch attached (the patch will break the &quot;openjpa.out&quot; property processing - which imho. should not be needed at all.)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12855981" author="ppoddar@apache.org" created="Mon, 12 Apr 2010 15:27:32 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks Frank for the patch. I agree that the usage of existing &quot;-s&quot; or &quot;-d&quot; option to javac is the proper way to control the output rather than a redundant -Aout flag. As far as I recall, however, the values of -s/-d switches were not available consistently within the annotation processing environment &amp;#8211; but I admit that I did not pay enough attention or research sufficiently to output control at the time of writing the processor. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will prefer to apply your patch. Will you please update us on which compilers have you tried the patch with? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12856035" author="fs5" created="Mon, 12 Apr 2010 16:51:04 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I tested my patch under Sun JDK 1.6.0_18 with Ant 1.7.1 and with eclipse 3.5.2 (with the same JDK) - but with only a few model classes. The patch should still be tested with a somewhat larger amount of entity classes.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
